<div class="book-text"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+64</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div>
<p>ImagôÙine the folôÙlowôÙing time travel probôÙlem:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>You reôÙcieve a winôÙning lotôÙtery numôÙber from the fuôÙture. What is the probôÙaôÙbilôÙity of winôÙning the lotôÙtery usôÙing that numôÙber?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Now, one might naively asôÙsume the chance is 100%. But in fact, the acôÙtual probôÙaôÙbilôÙity is only <em>slightly</em> betôÙter than if you guessed ranôÙdomly, and this can be verôÙiôÙfied exôÙperôÙiôÙmenôÙtally.</p>
<p>In orôÙder to avoid makôÙing seôÙriôÙous misôÙtakes and maxôÙiôÙmize sucôÙcess when time travôÙelôÙling, it is imôÙporôÙtant to have a clear unôÙderôÙstandôÙing of this and other seemôÙing paraôÙdoxes that can arise, and for that we must start with the baôÙsics.</p>
<h2 id="toc0"><span>CaôÙuôÙsalôÙity</span></h2>
<p>When disôÙcussing time travel, it is ofôÙten conôÙveôÙnient to disôÙcuss things in terms of &#8220;alôÙterôÙnate timeôÙliôÙnes&#8221;, reôÙferred to as <strong>world lines</strong>. While it is an open quesôÙtion whether other world lines are &#8220;acôÙtuôÙally reôÙal&#8221; in a philoôÙsophôÙiôÙcal sense, the conôÙcluôÙsions that can be drawn usôÙing this model are conôÙsisôÙtently borne out by exôÙperôÙiôÙmenôÙtal reôÙsults, and it serves as a useôÙful menôÙtal model for unôÙderôÙstandôÙing time travel.</p>
<div class="inset" style="width:30%;"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/44/Inachis_io_Lill-Jansskogen.JPG" style="width:100%;display:block;" alt="Inachis_io_Lill-Jansskogen.JPG" class="image" /> <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/89/Cyclone_Catarina_from_the_ISS_on_March_26_2004.JPG" style="width:100%;display:block;margin-bottom:5px;" alt="Cyclone_Catarina_from_the_ISS_on_March_26_2004.JPG" class="image" />
<p>In theôÙory, the air curôÙrents from a sinôÙgle butôÙterôÙfly wing beat could beôÙcome the deôÙcidôÙing facôÙtor in a hurôÙriôÙcane's forôÙmaôÙtion.</p>
</div>
<p>In some cases, the preôÙcise seôÙquence of events in a world line can be draôÙmatôÙiôÙcally inôÙfluôÙenced by a casôÙcade of events, startôÙing with some small <strong>predôÙiôÙcatôÙing event</strong>. This pheôÙnomôÙeôÙnon is reôÙferred to as a <strong>biôÙfurôÙcaôÙtion</strong>, and it is useôÙful to think of a world lines as &#8216;splitôÙting&#8217; into two or more sepôÙaôÙrate lines.</p>
<p>The typôÙiôÙcal exôÙamôÙple of this is the <em>butôÙterôÙfly efôÙfect</em>, ãnamed for the idea that due to the chaotic naôÙture of weather sysôÙtems, a sinôÙgle flap of a butôÙterôÙfly's wing could beôÙcome the deôÙcidôÙing facôÙtor in the forôÙmaôÙtion or strength of a hurôÙriôÙcane.</p>
<p>In practice, predôÙiôÙcatôÙing events are both a blessôÙing and a curse: while very useôÙful for modôÙiôÙfyôÙing past events, careôÙful preôÙcauôÙtions are reôÙquired to avoid inôÙadôÙverôÙtent changes.</p>
<p>SuprisôÙingly, it is also not unôÙcomôÙmon for two or more world lines to sponôÙtaôÙneously conôÙverge to nearly idenôÙtiôÙcal seôÙquences of events. These event seôÙquences comôÙmon to mulôÙtiôÙple world lines are reôÙferred to as <strong>atôÙtracôÙtor fields</strong>, and it is useôÙful to think of world lines as &#8220;mergôÙing toôÙgethôÙer&#8221; into one.</p>
<p>A real world exôÙamôÙple of an atôÙtracôÙtor field is the one surôÙroundôÙing the fall of the <a href="/scp-140">DaeôÙvites</a>. ReôÙgardôÙless of the preôÙcise date, be it 500 BC or 500 AD, their fall apôÙpears to lead inôÙevitably to the events in the ReôÙnaisôÙsance peôÙriod up to the preôÙsent.</p>
<p>ClasôÙsiôÙcal thought about chaotic sysôÙtems would lead one to beôÙlieve that nearly every small event, every nuôÙclear deôÙcay, proôÙtein fold, or cosôÙmic ray, would reôÙsult in large-scale biôÙfurôÙcaôÙtions. HowôÙever, in the conôÙtext of time travel, this does not apôÙpear to be the genôÙeral case: a small change may trigôÙger a small-scale temôÙpoôÙrary biôÙfurôÙcaôÙtion, but the two world lines quickly re-conôÙverge. This may be thought of as a genôÙerôÙalôÙizaôÙtion of the prinôÙciôÙple of least acôÙtion, in as much as &#8220;rewritôÙing hisôÙtoôÙry&#8221; can be conôÙsidôÙered an &#8220;acôÙtion&#8221;. This idea will be exôÙplained more forôÙmally in chapôÙter 3, but this apôÙproxôÙiôÙmaôÙtion is good enough for now.</p>
<p>A <strong>timeôÙline diôÙaôÙgram</strong> is a way of graphôÙiôÙcally repôÙreôÙsentôÙing the difôÙferôÙent types of caôÙusal reôÙlaôÙtionôÙships that can ocôÙcur when time travôÙelôÙling. There are many difôÙferôÙent ways one can draw a timeôÙline diôÙaôÙgram; the style used in this text is one of the most comôÙmon styles.</p>
<p>Here is an exôÙamôÙple diôÙaôÙgram showôÙing time travel beôÙing used to modôÙify the past to change an unôÙdeôÙsirôÙable event <span class="math-inline">$E$</span> and enôÙsure that deôÙsirôÙable event <span class="math-inline">$E'$</span> ocôÙcurs inôÙstead.</p>
<p><iframe src="/time-travel-ch1/html/e084ad8f82ec25f36ee88de39414bf560b820d60-844792297682343174" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" class="html-block-iframe"></iframe></p>
<p>In this diôÙaôÙgram, the douôÙble bar at the left inôÙdiôÙcates the beôÙginôÙning of a world line as it perôÙtains to the chart. The origôÙiôÙnal world line is repôÙreôÙsented with the horôÙiôÙzonôÙtal line, which goes unôÙtil <span class="math-inline">$E$</span> ocôÙcurs. The pair of dashed lines exôÙtendôÙing from it corôÙreôÙspond to the time disôÙplaceôÙments inôÙtended to corôÙrect E. In this case the disôÙplaceôÙment we care about is on top, the botôÙtom one is a reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment disôÙcussed in the next secôÙtion. The top disôÙplaceôÙment trigôÙgers a predôÙiôÙcatôÙing event repôÙreôÙsented by the split, and then the world line evenôÙtuôÙally biôÙfurôÙcates into the secôÙond one in which <span class="math-inline">$E'$</span> ocôÙcurs inôÙstead.</p>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>No ExôÙerôÙcises</span></h4>
<hr />
<h2 id="toc2"><span>DisôÙplaceôÙments</span></h2>
<div class="inset">
<p>The xyank is named afôÙter <a href="/iteration-0">Dr. ThadôÙdeus Xyank</a>, who disôÙcovôÙered many of the theôÙoôÙretôÙiôÙcal founôÙdaôÙtions of time travel in the 1950s and 60s.</p>
</div>
<p>In orôÙder to quanôÙtify time travel, we meaôÙsure the toôÙtal <strong>temôÙpoôÙral disôÙplaceôÙment</strong>, repôÙreôÙsented with <span class="math-inline">$\xi$</span>, to deôÙscribe 'how much' time travel a given event is. TemôÙpoôÙral disôÙplaceôÙment is meaôÙsured in <strong>xyanks</strong> (abôÙbreôÙviôÙated &quot;Xn&quot;) equivôÙaôÙlent to 1&#160;kg s<sup>3</sup>. By conôÙvenôÙtion, posôÙiôÙtive valôÙues are used to repôÙreôÙsent disôÙplaceôÙments into the fuôÙture, and negôÙaôÙtive valôÙues repôÙreôÙsent disôÙplaceôÙments into the past.</p>
<p>The First Law of Time Travel states that, given an obôÙject of mass <span class="math-inline">$m$</span> and the disôÙplaceôÙment inôÙterôÙval <span class="math-inline">$t$</span> the obôÙject travôÙels, the toôÙtal disôÙplaceôÙment is equal to the mass times the inôÙterôÙval cubed:</p>
<span class="equation-number">(1)</span>
<div class="math-equation" id="equation-1">\begin{align} \xi = m\; t^3 \end{align}</div>
<p>For exôÙamôÙple, if I had an apôÙpaôÙraôÙtus caôÙpaôÙble of 1 ôçXn, it could disôÙplace 1 milôÙligram of matôÙter 1 secôÙond, 1&#160;ôçg of matôÙter 10 secôÙonds, etc.</p>
<h4 id="toc3"><span>ExôÙerôÙcises</span></h4>
<ol>
<li>An 7&#160;kg obôÙject is disôÙplaced by 4 Xn. Does it end up in the past or the fuôÙture, and how far?</li>
<li>Given a 5&#160;kg test mass, what disôÙplaceôÙment would be needed to send it 5 minôÙutes into the fuôÙture?</li>
<li>A 62.0&#160;kg huôÙman is disôÙplaced 46.7 kXn at 5:00 on MonôÙday, when does he arôÙrive?</li>
<li><em>AdôÙvanced</em> A cerôÙtain obôÙject starts out weighôÙing 0.450&#160;kg. The obôÙject is reôÙpeatôÙedly disôÙplaced 5 Xn into the fuôÙture, douôÙbling its mass beôÙtween disôÙplaceôÙments. In the limit, how far into the fuôÙture will the obôÙject ulôÙtiôÙmately be disôÙplaced, not countôÙing elapsed time beôÙtween disôÙplaceôÙments?</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2 id="toc4"><span>ReôÙacôÙtion DisôÙplaceôÙments</span></h2>
<p>The SecôÙond Law of Time Travel states that for any disôÙplaceôÙment, there must be an equal and opôÙpoôÙsite disôÙplaceôÙment, or, the sum of all disôÙplaceôÙments is zero.</p>
<span class="equation-number">(2)</span>
<div class="math-equation" id="equation-2">\begin{align} \sum \xi = 0 \end{align}</div>
<p>As a reôÙsult, in orôÙder to genôÙerôÙate a disôÙplaceôÙment to move some obôÙject through time, an equal and opôÙpoôÙsite reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment is also genôÙerôÙated that moves some other obôÙject in the opôÙpoôÙsite diôÙrecôÙtion.</p>
<div class="inset" style="width:35%;"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/05/STS-134_solid_rocket_booster_segment_stacking.jpg" style="width:100%;display:block;margin-bottom:5px;" alt="STS-134_solid_rocket_booster_segment_stacking.jpg" class="image" />
<p>A 225 ton granôÙite balôÙlast mass used in the ChronomeôÙter UpôÙscale NegaôÙtion Test in MelôÙborne, AusôÙtralia.</p>
</div>
<p>In curôÙrent real-world apôÙpliôÙcaôÙtions, the abôÙsolute disôÙplaceôÙment valôÙues achieved are inôÙcredôÙiôÙbly tiny, usuôÙally on the orôÙder of a few nanoxyanks or less. As a reôÙsult, comôÙmerôÙcial apôÙpliôÙcaôÙtions genôÙerôÙally use an apôÙproôÙpriôÙately-sized balôÙlast mass to limit the toôÙtal reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment inôÙterôÙval. In some cases the reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment can even be disôÙsiôÙpated into the equipôÙment or its surôÙroundôÙings withôÙout needôÙing a balôÙlast mass, howôÙever for safety reaôÙsons this is genôÙerôÙally not done exôÙcept at exôÙtremely low disôÙplaceôÙments.</p>
<p>HowôÙever, the reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment can have useôÙful apôÙpliôÙcaôÙtions in obôÙservôÙing the reôÙsults of time travel: an obôÙject so disôÙplaced will reôÙmain unôÙafôÙfected by the changes caused by the prinôÙciôÙpal disôÙplaceôÙment, alôÙlowôÙing for comôÙparôÙisons across world lines. In the case of a perôÙson, they would be able to reôÙmemôÙber the events of their origôÙiôÙnal world line.</p>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>ExôÙerôÙcises</span></h4>
<ol>
<li>A reôÙsearcher disôÙplaces an alôÙpha parôÙtiôÙcle (m = 6.646e-27&#160;kg) 1 day into the past. The reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment is used to reôÙtain the conôÙtents of a hard drive (m = 0.327&#160;kg). How long must the reôÙsearcher wait beôÙfore exôÙamôÙinôÙing the hard drive?</li>
<li>An inôÙteôÙgrated cirôÙcuit needs to genôÙerôÙate a disôÙplaceôÙment of -68.3 fXn per clock as part of its opôÙerôÙaôÙtions. BeôÙcause of the senôÙsiôÙtive naôÙture of the cirôÙcuit, the toôÙtal reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaceôÙment time needs to be limôÙited to unôÙder 15.0&#160;ps per clock. How large does the balôÙlast need to be?</li>
<li><em>AdôÙvanced</em> In relôÙaôÙtivôÙity, parôÙtiôÙcles that are movôÙing close to the speed of light gain adôÙdiôÙtional mass acôÙcordôÙing to their speed, by a facôÙtor of <span class="math-inline">$\gamma = 1 / \sqrt{1-v^2/ãc^2}$</span>. If a proôÙton travôÙelôÙling at 0.5c is disôÙplaced 1 year into the fuôÙture, and the reôÙacôÙtion disôÙplaces a secôÙond proôÙton at rest, how far into the past does the secôÙond proôÙton end up?</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2 id="toc6"><span>CurôÙrent LimôÙiôÙtaôÙtions</span></h2>
<p>The funôÙdaôÙmenôÙtal enôÙergy of disôÙplaceôÙment deôÙscribes the theôÙoôÙretôÙiôÙcal limit on the amount of enôÙergy reôÙquired to achieve a given disôÙplaceôÙment, and is apôÙproxôÙiôÙmately 4.95e-21&#160;J/ãXn. the HowôÙever, modôÙern techôÙniques reôÙquire orôÙders of magôÙniôÙtude more enôÙergy: The curôÙrent best, the TachyôÙonic Ion ManôÙual EmisôÙsion and OriôÙgin UniôÙfiôÙcaôÙtion TransôÙmitôÙter (TIMEôÙOUT) exôÙperôÙiôÙment at CERN, reôÙquires on the orôÙder of 1e20&#160;J/ãXn! To put that into perôÙspecôÙtive, one Xn costs more than the enôÙtire enôÙergy conôÙsumpôÙtion of the planet in 2013.</p>
<p>TechôÙniques that funcôÙtion at amôÙbiôÙent conôÙdiôÙtions reôÙquire still more enôÙergy, limôÙitôÙing the types of tarôÙgets that can be used to just those that are staôÙble unôÙder vacôÙuum at cryoôÙgenic temôÙperôÙaôÙtures.</p>
<p>FiôÙnally, no curôÙrently known techôÙniques are caôÙpaôÙble of reôÙliôÙably disôÙplacôÙing a tarôÙget into the past in a way that keeps the tarôÙget inôÙtact - even a very small misôÙmatch in the calôÙiôÙbraôÙtion on curôÙrent techôÙniques will conôÙvert the tarôÙget into an as-yet-unôÙknown form of matôÙter on disôÙplaceôÙment. ForôÙtuôÙnately, this limôÙiôÙtaôÙtion does not apôÙpear to apôÙply to forôÙward disôÙplaceôÙments.</p>
<p>Due to these limôÙiôÙtaôÙtions, transôÙport of peoôÙple, obôÙjects, or anôÙiôÙmals into the past is largely out of the quesôÙtion. HowôÙever, it is relôÙaôÙtively straightôÙforôÙward to transôÙmit digôÙiôÙtal inôÙforôÙmaôÙtion usôÙing streams of parôÙtiôÙcles and senôÙsiôÙtive deôÙtecôÙtors. ApôÙpaôÙraôÙtus caôÙpaôÙble of reôÙceivôÙing such streams was first deôÙvelôÙoped in 1991, placôÙing a hard cap on the earôÙliôÙest date that one can reôÙliôÙably send inôÙforôÙmaôÙtion to. ChapôÙter 5 covôÙers deôÙtails of retroôÙcausal transôÙmisôÙsion schemes used for this purôÙpose.</p>
<p>AnôÙother imôÙporôÙtant apôÙpliôÙcaôÙtion of time travel is in comôÙputôÙing. Many newer miôÙcroôÙprocesôÙsors take adôÙvanôÙtage of retroôÙcaôÙusal conôÙnecôÙtions as part of their branch preôÙdicôÙtion and cache prefetch hardôÙware, enôÙabling much higher perôÙforôÙmance and clock speeds than beôÙfore. This is not withôÙout its limôÙiôÙtaôÙtions - it is very difôÙfiôÙcult to reôÙliôÙably transôÙmit high-enôÙtropy inôÙforôÙmaôÙtion to the past - but sigôÙnifôÙiôÙcant adôÙvances have been made with this techôÙnolôÙogy. The reaôÙson for this limôÙiôÙtaôÙtion is covôÙered in chapôÙter 2, and chapôÙter 6 goes into deôÙtail about how retroôÙcausal conôÙnecôÙtions can be used for inôÙteôÙgrated cirôÙcuits.</p>
<p>Based on transôÙmisôÙsions reôÙceived from our fuôÙture, it is beôÙlieved that most, if not all, of these limôÙiôÙtaôÙtions will evenôÙtuôÙally be overôÙcome, but as yet nothôÙing more speôÙcific about time travel techôÙnolôÙogy has been reôÙceived.</p>
<h4 id="toc7"><span>No ExôÙerôÙcises</span></h4>
</div>
